8 F. 1. Any executive or administrative state, county, or
9 municipal officer who violates his or her duties under this chapter
10 may be subject to action by the Governor in the exercise of his or
11 her authority under the Oklahoma Constitution and state law. The
12 Governor may initiate judicial proceedings in the name of the state
